                    <p>Every dog is a unique animal, no two are ever the same. Therefore it stands to reason that they
                        won't always respond in the same way to any singular training method. Although there are various
                        general responses we could reasonably expect, there is no one cookie cutter approach to how we
                        should communicate with them. My job is to teach you to how to establish rules and boundaries
                        based on your dog's temperament and personality.</p>
                    <p>Dogs learn best in a familiar, safe environment, free of outside distractions and disruptions.
                        That's why in order to ensure your dog receives the ideal learning experience, I come directly
                        to your home where they will have the most controlled and neutral setting. Most behaviors a dog
                        exhibits stem from their home environment and how they respond to the established routine. After
                        assessing your current household dynamics and making the necessary adjustments, I will then
                        teach you how to effectively communicate with and be confident with leading your dog. Of course,
                        no dog lives in a vacuum, so once we have made suitable progress with your dog's training and
                        responsiveness we will gradually introduce distracting elements and environments to test their
                        understanding of the expectations placed upon them.</p>
